k=[]
def recursion_binarysearchvalues(L, v):
    low=0
    high=len(L)-1
    mid=(low+high)//2
    if L[mid]==v:
        k.append((mid,L[mid]))
        return k
    elif(L[mid]<v):
        k.append((mid,L[mid]))
        recursion_binarysearchvalues(L[mid+1: ],v)
    else:
        k.append((mid,L[mid]))
        recursion_binarysearchvalues(L[:mid-1],v)
    return k
print(recursion_binarysearchvalues(["a","b","c"],"c"))
